gomodel:SYNGO_1976  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 25/11/2017 eg\nEvidence for activity-dependent release is provided by the study by Lochner et al. (2005) PMID 16555239. Accordingly the site of action is supposedly the synaptic cleft or the perisynaptic space. Experimental description: Low density primary cultures of dissociated neurons fromembryonic day 18 rat hippocampi were prepared essentiallyas described previously (Banker and Goslin, 1998)\"\n\n26/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed eGFP-tPA is of rat species; \"The rat tPA gene used in these con-structs contained t....\"" ;
